			<header class="comment-header">
								<div class="comment-author-avatar">
					<img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/92698a87aed15079c9ab09aca69dbe7e?s=40&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/92698a87aed15079c9ab09aca69dbe7e?s=80&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-40 photo' height='40' width='40' />				</div>
				<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
					<cite class="fn comment-author vcard">Dan</cite>
					<a href="https://www.subtraction.com/2007/04/05/the-wii-as-s/#comment-37464" class="comment-date-time">
						<time datetime="2007-04-10T07:13:24-04:00">
						Tue 10 Apr 2007 at 7:13 am						</time>
					</a>
									</div><!-- .comment-meta .commentmetadata -->
			</header>

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>It so complicated to carry around so you end up convincing your friends to buy one so you don&#8217;t have to drag yours along all the time. 😉</p>
				<div class="reply">
								</div><!-- .reply -->
			</div>
		</article><!-- #comment-## -->
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="li-comment-37465">
		<article id="comment-37465" class="comment-article">
			<header class="comment-header">
								<div class="comment-author-avatar">
					<img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/7a372d751c902fd8264783164fabfa89?s=40&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/7a372d751c902fd8264783164fabfa89?s=80&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-40 photo' height='40' width='40' />				</div>
				<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
					<cite class="fn comment-author vcard">Lisa</cite>
					<a href="https://www.subtraction.com/2007/04/05/the-wii-as-s/#comment-37465" class="comment-date-time">
						<time datetime="2007-04-12T17:56:41-04:00">
						Thu 12 Apr 2007 at 5:56 pm						</time>
					</a>
									</div><!-- .comment-meta .commentmetadata -->
			</header>

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>So why don&#8217;t one of you create a carry case?  Think a flat H-shape the user would put on the floor and then place the Wii upon.  The H legs would wrap up, perhaps snap together.  (You&#8217;d need extra H bars to keep it from sliding out of course.)</p>
<p>You could also add a way to coil and snap  the cables to the bundle.  It wouldn&#8217;t be integral or elegant, but it could look sharp and facilitate allow one-hand-carrying.  (And the mark-up could be huge.)</p>
				<div class="reply">
								</div><!-- .reply -->
			</div>
		</article><!-- #comment-## -->
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
			</ol><!-- .comment-list -->

			
		
		
	
	
